## FAQ

### General Questions

**Q: Is KeepWise free?**  
A: Yes, KeepWise is completely free with no in-app purchases or subscriptions.

**Q: Does KeepWise require internet connection?**  
A: No, KeepWise works 100% offline. No internet connection is required or used.

**Q: Is my data safe?**  
A: Yes! All your data is stored locally on your device with AES-256 encryption. We never collect or transmit your data.

**Q: Can I sync my data across devices?**  
A: Currently, KeepWise does not support cloud sync. All data is stored locally on your device for maximum privacy.

### Using the App

**Q: How do I set up my PIN?**  
A: When you first open KeepWise, you'll be prompted to create a 6-digit PIN. Enter it twice to confirm.

**Q: I forgot my PIN. How can I reset it?**  
A: Unfortunately, for security reasons, there's no way to recover a forgotten PIN. You'll need to reinstall the app, which will clear all data and allow you to set a new PIN.

**Q: How do I add a transaction?**  
A: 
1. Tap the **+** button on the home screen
2. Select a category
3. Enter the amount
4. Add an optional description
5. Select the date
6. Tap **Save**

**Q: Can I edit or delete transactions?**  
A: Yes! Tap any transaction to view details, then tap **Edit** to modify it or **Delete** to remove it.

**Q: How do I change the default currency?**  
A: Go to **Settings** → **Default Currency** and select your preferred currency.

**Q: Can I export my data?**  
A: Yes! Go to **Settings** → **Export Data** to save your transactions as a CSV file.

**Q: What currencies are supported?**  
A: KeepWise supports 10 currencies: SGD, USD, EUR, GBP, JPY, CNY, MYR, THB, AUD, and CAD.

### Troubleshooting

**Q: The app won't open / crashes on launch**  
A: Try these steps:
1. Force close the app
2. Restart your device
3. Update to the latest iOS version
4. Reinstall the app (note: this will delete all data)

**Q: My transactions disappeared**  
A: This shouldn't happen as data is stored locally. If it does:
1. Check if you're using the correct PIN
2. Ensure you haven't cleared app data
3. Report the issue on GitHub with details

**Q: Face ID / Touch ID not working**  
A: Currently, KeepWise uses PIN authentication only. Biometric authentication is planned for a future update.

**Q: Can't enter amounts correctly**  
A: The amount entry uses a calculator-style input:
- Type digits from right to left
- Always shows 2 decimal places
- Example: Type "1234" to get "12.34"

**Q: Date picker not showing**  
A: Make sure you've selected the "Custom" date option to see the date picker.

### Data & Privacy

**Q: Where is my data stored?**  
A: All data is stored locally on your device using iOS secure storage (Keychain and AsyncStorage).

**Q: Can you access my data?**  
A: No, we cannot access your data. It never leaves your device.

**Q: What happens if I uninstall the app?**  
A: All your data will be permanently deleted. Make sure to export your data first if you want to keep it.

**Q: Is my data encrypted?**  
A: Yes, your PIN is encrypted using AES-256 encryption, and encryption keys are stored in iOS Keychain.

